        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 1 at 12:06AM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 1206 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Mount Orab,
moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail may cause minor damage to vegetation.

Locations impacted include...
State Route 32 at US Route 68, Mowrystown, Sardinia, Greenbush,
Locust Ridge, Buford, and Mount Orab.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.
</description>
